KKR, TPG Plan to Establish Businesses in Brazil, FT Reports

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-05-04T04:44:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/kkr-tpg-plan-to-establish-businesses-in-brazil-ft-reports.html
KKR & Co. and TPG Capital, the U.S.
private-equity firms, are planning to set up offices in  Brazil ,
the Financial Times reported, citing unidentified people in the
buyout business.  Both firms are looking for leaders who will then recruit
start-up teams of five or six people, the newspaper said.  Other buyout firms, such as Apax Partners LLP, Permira
Advisers LLP and BC Partners Ltd. may also move into Brazil, the
FT said.  TPG declined to comment and KKR didnâ€™t respond to a request
for comment, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
